        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued April 19 at 3:33PM CDT until April 19 at 4:00PM CDT by NWS Midland/Odessa TX</headline>
        <description>At 333 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 24 miles northeast
of Big Lake, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Tennis ball size hail and 70 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect hail
damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles. Expect
considerable tree damage. Wind damage is also likely to
mobile homes, roofs, and outbuildings.

This severe thunderstorm will remain over mainly rural areas of
southeastern Glasscock and northeastern Reagan Counties.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
